{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place shallots and garlic into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add water, cherry jam, balsamic vinegar, butter, ¼ tsp salt and ⅛ tsp pepper into mixing bowl. Place Varoma into position, weigh in pork tenderloin and carrots. Arrange carrots around pork, season with ¼ tsp salt and ⅛ tsp pepper, secure Varoma lid and steam <nobr>20 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Remove Varoma, transfer pork and carrots to a serving platter and keep warm.","Add flour into mixing bowl, place simmering basket instead of measuring cup onto mixing bowl lid and cook <nobr>6 min\/Varoma\/speed 3<\/nobr>. Insert measuring cup and purée <nobr>30 sec\/speed 8<\/nobr>. Slice tenderloin into medallions and drizzle with cherry sauce. Garnish with cherries and chopped parsley and serve hot."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["1 oz shallots, in pieces","1 garlic clove","8 oz water","2 oz cherry jam","1 tsp balsamic vinegar","½ oz unsalted butter","½ tsp salt, divided","¼ tsp ground black pepper, divided","16 oz pork tenderloin","12 oz baby rainbow carrots, peeled, halved lengthwise","1 tbsp all-purpose flour","fresh cherries, pitted, halved, to garnish (optional)","chopped parsley, to garnish"]}],"id":"r307134","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-ZqZjnbK59ts\/XZQIIKHT_wI\/AAAAAAAAcPk\/KuW9MWWrce0T3DJ992T1CqM52s3TpMyEQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_xn5_9Em4UiqYs3Cp.png","title":"Pork Tenderloin with Cherry Sauce","publishedAt":"2018-02-02T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"25 g","fat":"6 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"21 g","calories":"996 kJ \/ 238 kcal"},"usefulItems":"serving platter","hintsAndTricks":["The USDA Guidelines and National Pork Board recommend cooking pork chops, roasts and tenderloin to an internal temperature between 145° F (medium rare) and 160° F (medium), followed by a 3 minute rest."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","35m","4 portions"]}